                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12643061" author="jimk" created="Mon, 27 Oct 2008 21:10:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Chore is a task performed on a period in hbase.  The chore is run in its own thread. This base abstract class provides while loop and sleeping facility. If an unhandled exception, the threads exit is logged. Implementers just need to add checking if there is work to be done and if so, do it.  It&apos;s the base of several of the chore threads in hbase.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t subclass Chore if the task relies on being woken up for something to do, such as an entry being added to a queue, etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following classes are not Chores, because rather than repeating the same task over and over after a nap, they wait for a wake-up because there is something to do:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Leases, HMaster, CompactSplitThread, LogRoller, MemcacheFlusher.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BaseScanner (and subclasses),  and LogFlusher are Chores.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
